Data

News

Source: The Gdelt Project

Description: It provides events reported in articles published in the 65 live translated languages. The sample data we used was the latest 15 minute news data at 4pm, Tuesday.

Format: 61 columns total, but we are using id, latitude, longitude, city, origin_url only.

Weather

Source: CPC Global Daily Temperature

Description: - CPC .50x.50 Global Daily Temperature - Spatial Coverage: 0.50 - degree latitude x 0.50 - degree longitude grid (720x360). - Updated daily

Format: Max and Min tempertaure NetCDF4 files that can be directly downloaded from the link.

Interactive Map

Linear Regression

model1 <- lm(
  formula = sentiscore ~ Tmin,
  data = allData)
summary(model1)
##

## lm(formula = sentiscore ~ Tmin, data = allData)
## 
## Residuals:

## -21.763  -5.616  -3.198   5.876  61.141

## Coefficients:

## (Intercept)  3.56612    1.40392   2.540   0.0114 *
## Tmin         0.10304    0.08082   1.275   0.2030  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 9.692 on 482 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.003361,   Adjusted R-squared:  0.001293 
## F-statistic: 1.625 on 1 and 482 DF,  p-value: 0.203
ggplot(allData,
  aes(x = Tmin, y = sentiscore)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(y = predict(model1))) +
  labs(title = 'Intercept and slope with lm')

library(lme4)
model2 <- lmer(
  sentiscore ~ (Tmin|Tmax),
  data = allData)
summary(model2)
